arer visitors.Introductory sections discuss the tropical Pacific as an environment for birds, problems of birding on islands, and bird conservation. Appendixes include maps of the island groups and a thorough bibliography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBirdszHawaiixIdentification. 0aBirdszOceaniaxIdentification. 7aNATURE / Birdwatching Guides.2bisacsh1 aBerrett, Delwyn G., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBruner, Phillip L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691257761?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691257761423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691257761/original  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles